              <a:t>So contracts/ is the skeleton of the whole system. AgentDefinition is now a proper dataclass — when you read an agent YAML, it's parsed into AgentDefinition and typos become validation errors, not silent bugs. RuntimeMessage bridges LangChain's HumanMessage/AIMessage/ToolMessage to our format with extra fields like message_id, created_at, and artifact_refs. SessionState replaces ChatSession and is fully serializable to dict for persistence, plus it includes pending_notifications for background job completions. RagContract defines what every RAG pipeline returns — any code calling RAG gets a guaranteed shape. ToolDefinition captures rich metadata: whether a tool is read_only, destructive, or background_safe so the executor can make smarter decisions.</a:t>
            </a:r>
